-{"id":"frankenredis-rhd1","title":"redis parity: CONFIG RESETSTAT should reset command/error stats like Redis","description":"Vendored Redis configResetStatCommand in legacy_redis_code/redis/src/config.c resets server stats, command table stats, and error table stats, but local config_cmd only calls Store::reset_info_stats at crates/fr-store/src/lib.rs. Bring CONFIG RESETSTAT to Redis parity by resetting the command/error accounting surfaces exposed by INFO and related introspection, not just the current store-local counters.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T12:51:42.732537790Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T12:51:42.732537790Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"frankenredis-rhd1","title":"redis parity: CONFIG RESETSTAT should reset command/error stats like Redis","description":"Vendored Redis configResetStatCommand in legacy_redis_code/redis/src/config.c resets server stats, command table stats, and error table stats, but local config_cmd only calls Store::reset_info_stats at crates/fr-store/src/lib.rs. Bring CONFIG RESETSTAT to Redis parity by resetting the command/error accounting surfaces exposed by INFO and related introspection, not just the current store-local counters.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T12:51:42.732537790Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T13:08:33.345939384Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T13:08:33.343538999Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenredis-rhyk","title":"redis parity: CONFIG REWRITE should error without config file and surface rewrite failures","description":"Vendored Redis configRewriteCommand in legacy_redis_code/redis/src/config.c returns 'The server is running without a config file' when no config file is loaded and surfaces rewrite OS failures, but local config_cmd in crates/fr-command/src/lib.rs unconditionally returns OK for CONFIG REWRITE. Implement Redis-compatible CONFIG REWRITE parity, including the no-config-file error path and failure surface, and update the stale core_config/core_server conformance expectations that currently accept OK.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T12:51:42.715919092Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T12:53:30.000000000Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenredis-rk0","title":"Align replication offsets with byte-stream semantics","description":"Replication currently advances primary/ack offsets by one per AOF record, while PSYNC backlog replay and replica propagation operate on RESP byte streams. This misstates ROLE/INFO replication offsets and risks incorrect partial-resync boundaries once command sizes vary. Update offset accounting and backlog slicing to use encoded stream byte offsets, then add tests covering ROLE/INFO and partial-resync boundaries.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-22T23:45:03.118565425Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T23:51:57.059822715Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T23:51:57.059239256Z","close_reason":"Implemented and verified","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenredis-rna","title":"Implement MIGRATE with full key transfer semantics","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-03-23T07:33:05.850810809Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T07:47:43.733478842Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T07:47:43.732782383Z","close_reason":"MIGRATE fully implemented: parses all options (COPY/REPLACE/AUTH/AUTH2/KEYS), validates KEYS with empty key requirement, establishes real TCP connection with timeout, returns NOKEY for empty key list, IOERR for connection failures","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
